data.description: Charming 1905 built home in Stockwell, Indiana! This 3-bedroom, 1.5-bath gem is conveniently located near Lafayette, Frankfort, Lebanon, and the northside of Indianapolis, offering easy access to urban while maintaining the charm of small-town living. Nestled amidst mature trees, this picturesque property boasts a warm and inviting atmosphere. Step inside to find a cozy fireplace and elegant hardwood floors that add character to the spacious living spaces. First floor bathroom has been remodeled and updated yet retaining the original charm. The kitchen is a chef's dream, equipped with efficient appliances and ample storage. Parking is a breeze with a one-and-a-half-car garage, and you'll love spending time on the large, welcoming porch, perfect for relaxing after a long day. The house is ideally situated across from two parks, offering plenty of green spaces to enjoy with family and friends. Families will appreciate the close proximity to Cole Elementary, a mere 2 miles away, and the added benefit of residing in the acclaimed TSC school district, known for its award-winning education. Don't miss the chance to make this lovely colonial house your forever home. Experience the best of small-town living with easy access to everything you need. Act fast, as this gem won't stay on the market for long! Call now to schedule a view!
